import org.apache.spark.sql.SQLContext
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._ 
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._ 
//val df = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "true").option("inferSchema", "true").load("file:///Users/vshukla/Downloads/Spark-16-Tickets.csv")
val df = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "true").option("inferSchema", "true").load("/user/livy/sparkticketsjuly252016.csv")
val df1 = df.withColumn("DateTimeOpened2", toDate('DateTimeOpened))
df1.printSchema
df1.cache()
df1.registerTempTable("tickets")

%md
## How are support tickets trending per quarter?

result.msg: How are support tickets trending per quarter?

paragraphs.text:
%livy.sql 
SELECT year(DateTimeOpened2) as Year, quarter(DateTimeOpened2) as Quarter, count(distinct CaseNumber) as Cases FROM tickets group by year(DateTimeOpened2), quarter(DateTimeOpened2) order by year(DateTimeOpened2) asc, quarter(DateTimeOpened2) asc

%md
## How are customers trending per quarter?

result.msg: How are customers trending per quarter?

paragraphs.text:
%livy.sql
SELECT year(DateTimeOpened2) as Year, quarter(DateTimeOpened2) as Quarter, count(distinct Account) as Accounts FROM tickets group by year(DateTimeOpened2), quarter(DateTimeOpened2) order by year(DateTimeOpened2) asc, quarter(DateTimeOpened2) asc

%md
## Does the case severity affect speed of resolution?

result.msg: Does the case severity affect speed of resolution?

paragraphs.text:
%livy.sql 
select Age as Days,count(*) as Count
from tickets where array_contains(split(Severity,' '), "${Severity=S1,S1|S2|S3|S4}" )
group by Age
order by Age
